To determine how many tempos can lift 29,400 toys in one round, start by calculating the number of toys per tempo. Each box contains \(5 \times 12 = 60\) toys, and each tempo holds 98 boxes. Thus, the number of toys per tempo is:  
\[
98 \text{ boxes} \times 60 \text{ toys/box} = 5,\!880 \text{ toys}.
\]  
Next, divide the total number of toys by the capacity of one tempo to find the number of tempos needed:  
\[
\frac{29,\!400 \text{ toys}}{5,\!880 \text{ toys/tempo}} = 5 \text{ tempos}.
\]  
This matches option **B**.  

Answer: B
